OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,FAn MP has lost a High Court bid to be
OL,8,Flet back into his former constituency
OL,9,Foffice after being locked out
OL,10,Ffollowing his defection from the
OL,11,FConservatives to Reform.
OL,13,FAndrew Rosindell, who has represented
OL,14,Fthe Romford constituency in east
OL,15,FLondon since 2001, defected in January
OL,16,Fand was later locked out of the
OL,17,Fconstituency office he had occupied
OL,18,Ffor more than 20 years at Margaret
OL,19,FThatcher House in Romford.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,FThe MP began legal proceedings against
OL,8,Fthe Romford Conservative Association
OL,9,F(RCA), which runs the building, with
OL,10,Fhis lawyers telling a hearing on
OL,11,FMonday it had "taken the law into its
OL,12,Fown hands" and that he should be
OL,13,Fgranted an injunction allowing him
OL,14,F"full and unfettered" access.
OL,26,@sD@OOUtD@JO]vD@AOUvD@UO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,FThe RCA opposed the bid, with its
OL,8,Fbarristers telling the court in London
OL,9,Fthat it was "blindingly obvious" that
OL,10,FMr Rosindell's licence to use the
OL,11,Fpremises only applied when he was a
OL,12,FConservative and that he could "spy"
OL,13,Fon its activities in the run-up to the
OL,14,Flocal elections.
OL,16,FIn a ruling, Mr Justice Choudhury
OL,17,Frefused the injunction bid, stating Mr
OL,18,FRosindell's case was "intrinsically
OL,19,Fweak" and that he "ought to have
OL,20,Frealised that he had surrendered his
OL,21,Fright to occupy" his office.
OL,26,@qD@MOUqD@`O]tD@`OUtD@dO]zD@VOU{D@EO]{D@
OL,26,ASOU}D@PO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,FHe said: "It would have been obvious
OL,8,Fto him from the moment of defecting
OL,9,Fthat continued occupation would be
OL,10,Funsustainable."
OL,12,FThe judge continued that the need for
OL,13,Fthose using the building to "share a
OL,14,Fcommon cause" with the Conservative
OL,15,FParty "strikes me as not only
OL,16,Fnecessary ... but consistent with
OL,17,Fcommon sense", and that there was no
OL,18,Fevidence that Mr Rosindell had sought
OL,19,Falternative accommodation.
OL,26,@oD@JOUrD@OO]uD@]OUvD@MO]wD@GOUyD@MO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,FHe also ordered Mr Rosindell to pay
OL,8,F#23,000 of RCA's legal costs.
OL,10,FAdam Richardson, for the MP, told the
OL,11,Fcourt in written submissions that the
OL,12,Fagreement to use the building saw
OL,13,Fmonthly payments of around #1,250 in
OL,14,Freturn for exclusive use of an office
OL,15,Fat the site and full access for Mr
OL,16,FRosindell and his staff.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,FAfter the defection, the association
OL,8,Fsaid the agreement for him to use the
OL,9,Fbuilding was invalid and later changed
OL,10,Fthe locks without notice, with Mr
OL,11,FRosindell's staff only allowed to
OL,12,Fretrieve work items under supervision.
OL,14,FMr Richardson said: "The proper course
OL,15,Fwould have been to seek possession
OL,16,Fthrough the court.
OL,18,F"Instead, the respondent has taken the
OL,19,Flaw into its own hands.
OL,26,@vD@UOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,F"Such conduct is unlawful irrespective
OL,8,Fof the ultimate determination of any
OL,9,Fdispute as to the validity of the
OL,10,Farrangements."
OL,12,FThe barrister continued that the
OL,13,Flockout was "materially impairing" Mr
OL,14,FRosindell's ability to serve his
OL,15,Fconstituents and deprived him of
OL,16,Fsafety measures inside the building,
OL,17,Fincluding CCTV and a panic room.
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@NO]uD@MOUuD@bO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,FIn court, Tiffany Scott KC, for the
OL,8,Fassociation, said there was an
OL,9,F"implied term" in the agreement for Mr
OL,10,FRosindell to use the site that meant
OL,11,Fit would "terminate automatically upon
OL,12,FMr Rosindell leaving the Conservative
OL,13,FParty".
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@NO]sD@JOUuD@FO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1775049066
OL,3,CReform MP locked out of office after
OL,4,Cdefection loses High Court injunction
OL,5,Cbid
OL,7,FIn written submissions, she said the
OL,8,Fpremises were "key to the Conservative
OL,9,Fcampaign" in the upcoming local
OL,10,Felections in May and therefore it
OL,11,Fwould be "damaging to the RCA and the
OL,12,FConservative Party for the MP for a
OL,13,Frival political party to have free
OL,14,Faccess to the building".
OL,16,FMs Scott also said Mr Rosindell had
OL,17,F"chosen to take no steps to find any
OL,18,Falternative office space" and that
OL,19,FReform "ought also to be supporting
OL,20,Fhim".
OL,26,@pD@OOUqD@IO]sD@JOUvD@WO]yD@AOUzD@YO]{D@
OL,26,AHOU|D@DO]
